parse: Verb - Present Imperative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To despise, scorn, and show it by active insult, disregard. From kata and phroneo; to think against, i.e. Disesteem.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Genitive 2nd Person Singular
str2: You. The person pronoun of the second person singular; thou.
Youth, youthfulness. From neos; newness, i.e. Youthfulness.
But, except, however. Neuter plural of allos; properly, other things, i.e. contrariwise.

str2: A prolongation and middle voice form of a primary verb; to cause to be, i.e. to become, used with great latitude.

The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
